00:00:07.597 --> 00:00:10.666 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>As Wolf and the other civilians</i>
 <i>are about to complete their</i>

00:00:10.700 --> 00:00:13.168 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>hack, and regain control over</i>
 <i>the broadcast tower.</i>

00:00:13.201 --> 00:00:16.706 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>A surprise assault by a</i>
 <i>terraformer has interrupted</i>
 <i>their progress,</i>

00:00:16.739 --> 00:00:21.577 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>forcing Keiji to sacrifice the</i>
 <i>mission in favor of saving his</i>
 <i>teammates.</i>

00:00:21.611 --> 00:00:25.615 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>Despair weighs heavily on the</i>
 <i>crew as chances of a rescue</i>
 <i>are dashed.</i>

00:00:25.648 --> 00:00:28.451 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>But a voice from above</i>
 <i>reignites their hope.</i>

00:00:28.484 --> 00:00:32.788 position:13% line:77% align:start
 <i>Amelia Venkatesh now bears</i>
 <i>the burden of completing</i>
 <i>the mission alone.</i>

00:00:32.822 --> 00:00:40.429 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>Determined that their efforts</i>
 <i>not be in vain, Amelia pushes</i>
 <i>for her fearful teammates, and</i>
 <i>for her hero, Keiji Onizuka.</i>

00:00:41.330 --> 00:00:47.470 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>[gasping]</i>  We've still...
got a planet to save.

00:00:47.503 --> 00:00:50.206 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:00:50.239 --> 00:00:54.143 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>...</i>  Wolf... You got us right
to the finish line.

00:00:56.679 --> 00:01:03.854 position:5% line:77% align:start
 And Keiji... you fought so hard
 and endured so much, just to
 buy us time.

00:01:03.887 --> 00:01:08.157 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sob]

00:01:11.595 --> 00:01:16.500 position:16% line:83% align:start
Your sacrifices... will
 not be in vain!

00:01:31.315 --> 00:01:41.325 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:01:41.358 --> 00:01:51.368 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:01:51.401 --> 00:02:01.345 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:02:01.378 --> 00:02:11.388 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:02:11.421 --> 00:02:21.365 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:02:21.398 --> 00:02:31.409 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:02:31.442 --> 00:02:45.189 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:02:48.960 --> 00:02:50.862 position:30% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Petra Eheim)</i>
 <i>What's the plan Ichiro?</i>

00:02:50.895 --> 00:02:54.232 position:13% line:5% align:start
 <i>What happens if they can't</i>
 <i>restore communication?</i>

00:02:54.265 --> 00:02:59.470 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'll tell you "what" ...We'll be
up shits creek without a paddle.

00:02:59.504 --> 00:03:04.442 position:5% line:83% align:start
It's a huge risk...
Are you sure?

00:03:04.475 --> 00:03:06.711 position:5% line:89% align:start
I understand your concerns.

00:03:06.744 --> 00:03:09.848 position:5% line:89% align:start
Don't worry. They'll deliver.

00:03:19.524 --> 00:03:23.696 position:50% line:83% align:start
Ryuichi, can you
anchor a thread up top?

00:03:23.729 --> 00:03:27.833 position:5% line:83% align:start
I can't... I can
only do it once.

00:03:27.866 --> 00:03:30.736 position:5% line:83% align:start
That's why I was
given rank 70...

00:03:30.769 --> 00:03:34.840 position:19% line:83% align:start
Maybe... I... could...
[coughing]

00:03:35.908 --> 00:03:39.243 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crying]

00:03:39.277 --> 00:03:43.882 position:7% line:83% align:start
So... This is it? The bacteria
has overwhelmed my body.

00:03:43.916 --> 00:03:46.250 position:19% line:89% align:start
It wont be long now...

00:03:46.985 --> 00:03:50.889 position:10% line:83% align:start
We're going to die here...!
I'm sorry Keiji...

00:03:51.423 --> 00:03:55.494 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>...You sacrificed yourself</i>
 <i>for us, and we failed you.</i>

00:03:57.930 --> 00:04:04.303 position:24% line:83% align:start
(Terraformer Army)
Ji. Jo-Ji. Ji. Jo Jo.

00:04:04.336 --> 00:04:05.571 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:04:06.505 --> 00:04:09.408 position:19% line:89% align:start
Dammit! [attack grunt]

00:04:10.409 --> 00:04:14.948 position:27% line:89% align:start
[attack grunts]

00:04:14.981 --> 00:04:17.616 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Terraformer Army)</i>
 <i>Ji. Jo-Ji. Ji. Jo Jo.</i>

00:04:17.649 --> 00:04:19.785 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:04:20.552 --> 00:04:25.657 position:24% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Terraformer Army)</i>
 <i>Ji. Jo-Ji. Ji. Jo Jo.</i>

00:04:25.691 --> 00:04:28.594 position:13% line:83% align:start
Wanna make a bet? Who can
kill the most? [laugh]

00:04:28.627 --> 00:04:30.596 position:5% line:89% align:start
Don't get cocky, Akari...

00:04:30.629 --> 00:04:33.532 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Michelle)</i>
 <i>...You've got a promise</i>
 <i>to keep, remember?</i>

00:04:33.565 --> 00:04:34.633 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:04:35.434 --> 00:04:38.537 position:5% line:89% align:start
That kid's counting on you.

00:04:38.570 --> 00:04:41.306 position:5% line:89% align:start
Don't you dare let him down.

00:04:41.340 --> 00:04:42.474 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:04:42.942 --> 00:04:45.879 position:7% line:89% align:start
 My name is Sakurato Harukaze!

00:04:48.748 --> 00:04:50.850 position:50% line:83% align:start
 Do you know why
 we're going to Mars?

00:04:50.884 --> 00:04:53.052 position:33% line:83% align:start
 We're going to find a
 cure for your sickness.

00:04:53.086 --> 00:04:54.854 position:38% line:89% align:start
Really?

00:04:54.888 --> 00:04:57.891 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'm promising you!

00:04:57.924 --> 00:04:59.793 position:5% line:89% align:start
Be careful, Akari...

00:04:59.993 --> 00:05:02.729 position:21% line:89% align:start
I swear... I won't!

00:05:02.762 --> 00:05:04.063 position:5% line:89% align:start
Prove it then!

00:05:08.101 --> 00:05:12.071 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Thinking)</i>
 <i>We'll fight as long as we have</i>
 <i>to. We're counting on you...</i>

00:05:15.742 --> 00:05:20.947 position:5% line:89% align:start
[gasp] [uncontrollable coughing]

00:05:23.917 --> 00:05:28.755 position:21% line:83% align:start
I'll finish this...
I promise you!

00:05:32.559 --> 00:05:37.430 position:33% line:89% align:start
[deep sigh]

00:05:37.965 --> 00:05:40.835 position:24% line:5% align:start
 <i>(Amelia Thinking)</i>
 <i>Concentrate on using only</i>
 <i>what's necessary...</i>

00:05:40.868 --> 00:05:43.369 position:16% line:5% align:start
 <i>...Nothing else matters.</i>

00:05:45.906 --> 00:05:51.078 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Narrator)</i>
 <i>Whales dive to extreme depths,</i>
 <i>and for  extremely long periods.</i>

00:05:51.111 --> 00:05:55.749 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>To conserve energy, the marine</i>
 <i>mammal will shut down all</i>
 <i>unnecessary organs.</i>

00:05:55.783 --> 00:06:00.087 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Reeling from the affects of the</i>
 <i>toxin, Amelia follows her animal</i>
 <i>instincts.</i>

00:06:05.459 --> 00:06:08.429 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:06:09.630 --> 00:06:11.799 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Amelia Flash Back)</i>
 <i>You're missing out on the party.</i>

00:06:12.433 --> 00:06:14.468 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:06:15.603 --> 00:06:16.804 position:38% line:89% align:start
[exhale]

00:06:16.837 --> 00:06:20.641 position:5% line:83% align:start
They didn't forget to
tell you, did they?

00:06:20.674 --> 00:06:24.912 position:10% line:83% align:start
[sigh] Eh I don't think they
meant anything by it.

00:06:24.945 --> 00:06:28.549 position:10% line:77% align:start
I'm sure... they just didn't
want to interrupt my little run.

00:06:29.483 --> 00:06:31.752 position:5% line:89% align:start
They know me too well. [chuckle]

00:06:32.686 --> 00:06:36.457 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Amelia)</i>
 <i>You always seem to be training,</i>
 <i>more than any other recruit.</i>

00:06:36.490 --> 00:06:38.960 position:5% line:89% align:start
So what's it all for?

00:06:41.762 --> 00:06:45.499 position:7% line:89% align:start
Well... It's hard to explain.

00:06:45.532 --> 00:06:48.136 position:16% line:89% align:start
Is it just force of habit?

00:06:48.169 --> 00:06:52.506 position:47% line:77% align:start
Or is it sort of,
"practice makes perfect,
gym is life" kind of thing?

00:06:52.539 --> 00:06:55.043 position:19% line:89% align:start
No, nothing like that

00:06:55.076 --> 00:06:56.644 position:83% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:06:56.678 --> 00:06:59.180 position:10% line:83% align:start
It's not really the process
that interests me.

00:06:59.214 --> 00:07:02.951 position:24% line:83% align:start
How far I've run,
how much I lift...

00:07:02.984 --> 00:07:08.657 position:7% line:77% align:start
Fixate on the training, and I
guarantee, you'll end up losing
sight of the goal.

00:07:08.690 --> 00:07:10.659 position:33% line:89% align:start
Understand?

00:07:11.026 --> 00:07:13.194 position:58% line:89% align:start
Not really...

00:07:13.228 --> 00:07:17.098 position:24% line:83% align:start
When I became the
boxing world champion...

00:07:17.132 --> 00:07:19.100 position:5% line:89% align:start
What?! The world champion?

00:07:19.134 --> 00:07:21.136 position:5% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:07:21.169 --> 00:07:23.738 position:5% line:89% align:start
Wow I,  I had no idea.

00:07:23.772 --> 00:07:25.607 position:7% line:89% align:start
Heh. It's not that big a deal.

00:07:25.640 --> 00:07:29.177 position:16% line:83% align:start
It wasn't some dramatic
knockout.

00:07:29.210 --> 00:07:32.580 position:38% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Keiji)</i>
 <i>I won the match by</i>
 <i>narrow decision.</i>

00:07:32.614 --> 00:07:39.054 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>And for the first time in my</i>
 <i>life, I was overwhelmed with</i>
 <i>a sense of accomplishment.</i>

00:07:39.088 --> 00:07:41.057 position:5% line:83% align:start
(Amelia)
So all that training paid off?

00:07:41.090 --> 00:07:45.627 position:38% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Keiji)</i>
 <i>I train, so that if the time</i>
 <i>comes, I can push just a little</i>
 <i>bit further.</i>

00:07:45.660 --> 00:07:51.133 position:5% line:83% align:start
Whether it be today, or sometime
in the far distant future...

00:07:51.167 --> 00:07:56.138 position:7% line:77% align:start
When life calls for it, I know
I'll be ready to give a little
bit extra.

00:07:56.172 --> 00:07:57.974 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:07:58.307 --> 00:08:01.643 position:13% line:83% align:start
But, hey, maybe I'll catch
ya at the next party...

00:08:02.044 --> 00:08:03.112 position:44% line:89% align:start
Huh?

00:08:03.145 --> 00:08:05.014 position:5% line:89% align:start
For your run... [chuckle]

00:08:06.749 --> 00:08:08.884 position:33% line:89% align:start
[happy sigh]

00:08:11.721 --> 00:08:13.923 position:10% line:89% align:start
[satisfied sigh] Not bad...!

00:08:13.956 --> 00:08:15.124 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:08:16.892 --> 00:08:23.733 position:13% line:83% align:start
[sob] <i>I couldn't ask for a</i>
 <i>nicer final memory...</i>

00:08:24.934 --> 00:08:28.971 position:10% line:89% align:start
 <i>I only wish I'd told you...</i>

00:08:29.705 --> 00:08:32.675 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>old you ...that I</i>
 <i>love you, Keiji.</i>

00:08:34.210 --> 00:08:37.079 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>This can't be the end.</i>

00:08:37.113 --> 00:08:39.949 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>No, I'm not ready!</i>

00:08:42.918 --> 00:08:49.025 position:16% line:89% align:start
[choking] [heavy coughs]

00:08:53.763 --> 00:08:58.701 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>I wish I could</i>
 <i>have done more...</i>

00:09:01.004 --> 00:09:03.873 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>You protected us Keiji...</i>

00:09:03.907 --> 00:09:07.044 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>...Erika, you made reaching the</i>
 <i>comms room possible...</i>

00:09:07.077 --> 00:09:11.882 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>And Wolf, without you we would</i>
 <i>have never stood a chance.</i>

00:09:14.885 --> 00:09:20.057 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>What good am I if I can't do</i>
 <i>what it takes... like the rest</i>
 <i>of  you?</i>

00:09:20.090 --> 00:09:24.061 position:16% line:83% align:start
 <i>If I...If I could only</i>
 <i>have your strength...</i>

00:09:24.895 --> 00:09:26.897 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>I understand now, Keiji.</i>

00:09:26.930 --> 00:09:32.302 position:7% line:83% align:start
 <i>Why you always trained harder</i>
 <i>than everyone else.</i>

00:09:32.335 --> 00:09:38.141 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>Why Wolf never gave up being an</i>
 <i>engineer, even when faced with</i>
 <i>crippling depression.</i>

00:09:38.175 --> 00:09:41.244 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>You dig deep.</i>

00:09:41.278 --> 00:09:48.151 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>Deeper than you ever thought</i>
 <i>possible.</i>

00:09:48.785 --> 00:09:51.755 position:7% line:89% align:start
To give just a little more...

00:09:51.788 --> 00:09:54.292 position:19% line:89% align:start
 <i>So I'll do the same...</i>

00:09:54.325 --> 00:09:57.395 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I'll find that little</i>
 <i>extra within me...</i>

00:09:57.428 --> 00:10:02.233 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>And then, I will make sure your</i>
 <i>sacrifices mean something.</i>

00:10:02.966 --> 00:10:05.269 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>So here goes...</i>

00:10:09.407 --> 00:10:13.710 position:13% line:83% align:start
 <i>It'll all be over after I</i>
 <i>press this button...</i>

00:10:13.743 --> 00:10:17.348 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>I hope I've made you</i>
 <i>proud, Keiji...</i>

00:10:17.915 --> 00:10:21.185 position:21% line:89% align:start
[choking] [coughing]

00:10:34.332 --> 00:10:41.272 position:35% line:89% align:start
[growling]

00:10:41.305 --> 00:10:42.907 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>[computer glitch]</i>

00:10:42.940 --> 00:10:43.708 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:10:43.741 --> 00:10:45.209 position:5% line:89% align:start
You heard that, right?

00:10:46.377 --> 00:10:48.779 position:24% line:89% align:start
 <i>[tires screeching]</i>

00:10:53.117 --> 00:10:55.052 position:38% line:89% align:start
General, did they...

00:10:55.086 --> 00:10:58.055 position:7% line:89% align:start
Dammit... How did they do it?!

00:10:58.089 --> 00:11:01.759 position:10% line:77% align:start
We have a ten-second window
before the comms are fully
restored.

00:11:06.130 --> 00:11:08.065 position:33% line:89% align:start
[small gasp]

00:11:09.268 --> 00:11:12.069 position:30% line:89% align:start
[weak grunts]

00:11:12.104 --> 00:11:17.042 position:24% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Keiji flashback)</i>
 <i> When life calls for it, I know</i>
 <i> I'll be ready to give a little</i>
bit extra.

00:11:17.376 --> 00:11:20.012 position:33% line:83% align:start
 <i>(thinking)</i>
 <i>I've got to finish this...</i>

00:11:20.045 --> 00:11:22.981 position:16% line:89% align:start
 <i>I have to tell them...</i>

00:11:23.015 --> 00:11:27.685 position:10% line:83% align:start
 <i>I've got to restore my lungs</i>
 <i>and throat to speak.</i>

00:11:28.153 --> 00:11:33.724 position:30% line:83% align:start
[deep inhale]
[violent coughing]

00:11:34.893 --> 00:11:38.130 position:21% line:89% align:start
[choking back tears]

00:11:40.365 --> 00:11:46.805 position:24% line:89% align:start
I'll tell them...

00:11:52.878 --> 00:11:55.814 position:35% line:77% align:start
(officer)
Sir, comms have been
reestablished with the Annex 1!

00:11:55.847 --> 00:11:59.885 position:5% line:77% align:start
We can speculate all we want...
But we can't act until it's
confirmed.

00:11:59.918 --> 00:12:01.887 position:13% line:89% align:start
Don't miss a single word.

00:12:01.920 --> 00:12:05.491 position:35% line:65% align:start
SPEAK!
 <i>(Amelia)</i>
 <i>[violent coughing]</i>

00:12:08.394 --> 00:12:10.296 position:38% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Amelia)</i>
 <i>[gasps] Help us... help us...!</i>
 <i>Squad 4...!</i>

00:12:10.330 --> 00:12:13.232 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:12:13.266 --> 00:12:18.271 position:38% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Amelia)</i>
 <i>[gasps] Help us... help us...!</i>
 <i>Squad 4...!</i>

00:12:19.405 --> 00:12:22.308 position:13% line:89% align:start
Damn it... wasn't enough!

00:12:22.342 --> 00:12:25.211 position:21% line:83% align:start
She didn't say what
we needed to hear.

00:12:25.245 --> 00:12:29.215 position:30% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Comm Captain)</i>
 <i>That was the final communication</i>
 <i>we received from Annex 1.</i>

00:12:29.515 --> 00:12:31.451 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>...She didn't say what</i>
 <i>we needed</i>

00:12:31.484 --> 00:12:35.321 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>...Our hands are still tied!</i>

00:12:35.355 --> 00:12:37.490 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Amelia)</i>
 <i>Help... us...</i>

00:12:37.523 --> 00:12:38.558 position:44% line:89% align:start
Sí!

00:12:38.591 --> 00:12:39.292 position:44% line:89% align:start
Da!

00:12:39.325 --> 00:12:39.858 position:44% line:89% align:start
Ja!

00:12:39.892 --> 00:12:40.493 position:44% line:89% align:start
Yes!

00:12:40.526 --> 00:12:42.161 position:33% line:89% align:start
Understood!

00:12:49.969 --> 00:12:57.810 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>Keiji...Everyone... I'm so</i>
 <i>sorry. I  can't take another</i>
 <i>step.</i>

00:12:57.844 --> 00:13:04.117 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>After this transmission, I'll</i>
 <i>finally be with you. That's</i>
 <i>all I've ever wanted...</i>

00:13:04.917 --> 00:13:07.820 position:5% line:89% align:start
 <i>Let me stay with you forever...</i>

00:13:07.854 --> 00:13:09.822 position:35% line:89% align:start
Jo... Ji!

00:13:09.856 --> 00:13:12.426 position:5% line:89% align:start
Hurry...! Amelia's the last one!

00:13:12.459 --> 00:13:14.193 position:13% line:89% align:start
Don't worry we'll get her!

00:13:14.227 --> 00:13:17.096 position:35% line:83% align:start
Heads up! We're about
to have company!

00:13:17.130 --> 00:13:19.566 position:27% line:89% align:start
Jo... [hissing]

00:13:29.376 --> 00:13:31.178 position:38% line:89% align:start
 <i>[glitch]</i>

00:13:31.445 --> 00:13:32.313 position:38% line:89% align:start
Uh, sir?

00:13:32.346 --> 00:13:33.980 position:30% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Comm Captain)</i>
 <i>What is it?</i>

00:13:34.013 --> 00:13:38.319 position:7% line:77% align:start
Before we lost communication,
the radio tower transmitted
some observational data.

00:13:38.352 --> 00:13:44.224 position:10% line:71% align:start
According to this, the armed
rescue vessel that the Chinese
government launched, isSmuch
closer to Mars than we thought.

00:13:44.258 --> 00:13:45.726 position:5% line:89% align:start
Are you sure?

00:13:45.759 --> 00:13:48.228 position:30% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Comm officer)</i>
 <i>But that's not all... there are</i>
 <i>two other ships!</i>

00:13:48.262 --> 00:13:51.598 position:16% line:77% align:start
 <i>Three ships in total are</i>
 <i>currently advancing towards</i>
 <i>Mars!</i>

00:13:53.067 --> 00:13:57.071 position:5% line:77% align:start
Those pests were able to
briefly restore
communications with Earth

00:13:57.104 --> 00:14:01.241 position:5% line:77% align:start
While our mission remains
the same, this does rather
complicate things.

00:14:01.275 --> 00:14:05.012 position:5% line:83% align:start
We must capture the First
and Second immediately,

00:14:05.045 --> 00:14:07.414 position:5% line:83% align:start
then meet at the
rendezvous point.

00:14:07.448 --> 00:14:10.084 position:5% line:83% align:start
Then we get off this
shit hole planet.

00:14:11.585 --> 00:14:14.221 position:38% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Akari)</i>
 <i>Are comms back online?</i>

00:14:14.254 --> 00:14:18.626 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Michelle)</i>
 <i>No, they were up only briefly,</i>
 <i>but they've been disconnected.</i>

00:14:18.660 --> 00:14:20.562 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Akari)</i>
 <i>Then what's happened</i>
 <i>to the others?</i>

00:14:20.595 --> 00:14:25.467 position:19% line:77% align:start
I don't know. Maybe we
were knocked offline by
some backup system

00:14:25.500 --> 00:14:27.334 position:10% line:89% align:start
one built to prevent hacks.

00:14:27.368 --> 00:14:29.169 position:52% line:83% align:start
Then we need to
go back and help.

00:14:29.203 --> 00:14:31.205 position:41% line:83% align:start
We can't leave them
stranded at The Annex 1...

00:14:31.238 --> 00:14:34.908 position:7% line:83% align:start
No. We stick to the captain's
orders and head north.

00:14:34.942 --> 00:14:37.278 position:24% line:83% align:start
It's everyone best
chance of survival.

00:14:40.448 --> 00:14:43.050 position:5% line:89% align:start
[gasping]

00:14:43.083 --> 00:14:45.186 position:27% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Jared Anderson)</i>
 <i>Not what you expected</i>
 <i>heaven to look like?</i>

00:14:45.220 --> 00:14:48.956 position:5% line:83% align:start
Jared... I don't understand
how I'm still alive...

00:14:48.989 --> 00:14:53.194 position:5% line:83% align:start
I thought I was done
for. All that bacteria...

00:14:53.228 --> 00:14:58.433 position:19% line:83% align:start
Turns out she can make
her own antidote...

00:14:58.466 --> 00:15:01.236 position:19% line:77% align:start
 <i>a failsafe in case she</i>
 <i>accidentally infects her</i>
 <i>own team.</i>

00:15:01.269 --> 00:15:03.304 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>Her bacteria is</i>
 <i>incredibly potent,</i>

00:15:03.338 --> 00:15:07.208 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i>so just one injection of the</i>
 <i>antidote isn't enough for a</i>
 <i>full recovery.</i>

00:15:07.242 --> 00:15:09.477 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>But we're grateful she</i>
 <i>gave it to us at all.</i>

00:15:09.511 --> 00:15:11.546 position:5% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:15:13.114 --> 00:15:15.216 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>[glass shatter]</i>

00:15:15.250 --> 00:15:17.552 position:35% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Jared)</i>
 <i>The roaches swarmed Annex 1...</i>

00:15:17.585 --> 00:15:22.991 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>And immediately began</i>
 <i>dismantling it.</i>

00:15:23.024 --> 00:15:27.429 position:21% line:83% align:start
 <i>Their precision and</i>
 <i>speed was alarming.</i>

00:15:27.462 --> 00:15:32.434 position:7% line:77% align:start
 <i>One of them had transmitted a</i>
 <i>message from within the Annex 1</i>
 <i>before the ship was overrun,</i>

00:15:32.468 --> 00:15:34.969 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>but we don't know for</i>
 <i>certain what it said.</i>

00:15:35.003 --> 00:15:38.674 position:13% line:77% align:start
It might've been reporting
that the poison in the area
had dissipated.

00:15:38.707 --> 00:15:44.279 position:10% line:77% align:start
Since they likely no longer
consider the ship  a threat it
serves us no tactical use.

00:15:44.313 --> 00:15:46.348 position:7% line:89% align:start
We must continue to the north.

00:15:46.382 --> 00:15:47.483 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Amelia)</i>
 <i>[gasp]</i>
Huh?

00:15:47.516 --> 00:15:50.386 position:5% line:83% align:start
Captain, sir, there's something
I need to tell you...

00:15:50.419 --> 00:15:54.523 position:5% line:77% align:start
when I was in the comms room, I
could hear them on the line, but
I couldn't think straight,

00:15:54.557 --> 00:15:56.392 position:10% line:89% align:start
all I did was beg for help!

00:15:56.425 --> 00:16:00.028 position:19% line:83% align:start
I couldn't... get the
message to them.

00:16:00.061 --> 00:16:01.664 position:33% line:89% align:start
I blew it.

00:16:02.298 --> 00:16:04.400 position:19% line:89% align:start
Now no one is coming!

00:16:06.502 --> 00:16:11.140 position:5% line:77% align:start
(Shokichi)
Because of your efforts, we
able to connect to Earth.

00:16:11.173 --> 00:16:12.374 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:16:12.408 --> 00:16:15.511 position:5% line:77% align:start
For ten seconds, you
communicated with our
allied diplomats.

00:16:15.544 --> 00:16:20.583 position:5% line:77% align:start
And during that time, our
officer's transmitters
came back online,

00:16:20.616 --> 00:16:22.685 position:5% line:83% align:start
allowing them access
to the comms channel.

00:16:22.718 --> 00:16:24.788 position:44% line:89% align:start
Hm?

00:16:24.821 --> 00:16:27.223 position:5% line:89% align:start
You were successful.

00:16:27.256 --> 00:16:29.091 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:16:29.124 --> 00:16:30.459 position:19% line:89% align:start
Germany, do you read?

00:16:30.493 --> 00:16:33.028 position:16% line:89% align:start
Squad 4 has betrayed us!

00:16:33.062 --> 00:16:34.296 position:38% line:89% align:start
[grunt]

00:16:34.330 --> 00:16:37.634 position:24% line:83% align:start
Send back up! This
is Officer Davis!

00:16:37.667 --> 00:16:40.035 position:5% line:89% align:start
Inform the other allied nations!

00:16:43.172 --> 00:16:48.645 position:5% line:77% align:start
Those ten seconds you secured
changed the fate of this planet
and saved countless lives.

00:16:48.678 --> 00:16:53.048 position:5% line:77% align:start
Because of your bravery,
we may actually make it
off this awful planet

00:16:53.082 --> 00:16:56.118 position:5% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi)</i>
 <i>Thank you, Amelia.</i>
 <i>We owe you our lives.</i>

00:16:56.151 --> 00:17:03.226 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>And Thank you, Keiji, Wolf,</i>
 <i>Erika, Ryuichi, Ryuji!</i>

00:17:03.260 --> 00:17:08.665 position:5% line:71% align:start
 <i>We attempted to rendezvous with</i>
 <i>Akari and Michelle, but we were</i>
 <i>cut off by a large group of</i>
 <i>terraformars.</i>

00:17:08.698 --> 00:17:13.236 position:5% line:77% align:start
Once they were handled, we came
back to provide assistance to
you noncombatants.

00:17:13.270 --> 00:17:21.144 position:13% line:77% align:start
Then they found us, and we
assisted in your rescue,
using our air bikes.

00:17:21.177 --> 00:17:23.747 position:5% line:83% align:start
This mission has
taken many lives...

00:17:23.780 --> 00:17:26.249 position:5% line:83% align:start
...but in the end
we were successful.

00:17:26.283 --> 00:17:29.619 position:5% line:83% align:start
I'm honored to stand
among your ranks.

00:17:30.554 --> 00:17:40.564 position:44% line:89% align:start
 ♪

00:17:40.597 --> 00:17:50.608 position:44% line:89% align:start
 ♪

00:17:50.641 --> 00:17:57.715 position:44% line:89% align:start
 ♪

00:17:57.748 --> 00:18:03.186 position:5% line:77% align:start
And as for them... Hong is in
the dark about the details of
their squad's operation

00:18:03.219 --> 00:18:05.790 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>I bet that Xi knows how to get</i>
 <i>in touch with her comrades.</i>

00:18:06.424 --> 00:18:08.292 position:5% line:89% align:start
She'll wake up eventually,

00:18:08.326 --> 00:18:10.728 position:5% line:83% align:start
and when she does we'll
have her contact Liu.

00:18:10.761 --> 00:18:13.230 position:5% line:83% align:start
We'll tell him his
mission is a bust.

00:18:14.365 --> 00:18:17.234 position:5% line:83% align:start
Maybe then the
fighting will end.

00:18:17.635 --> 00:18:19.270 position:5% line:89% align:start
 It has to.

00:18:19.737 --> 00:18:22.873 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>We'll need each other's help</i>
 <i>to get out of here alive.</i>

00:18:22.907 --> 00:18:26.177 position:19% line:83% align:start
Really? That's rather
unfortunate.

00:18:26.210 --> 00:18:29.847 position:7% line:83% align:start
If this is true, I'm afraid I
can no longer be of assistance.

00:18:29.880 --> 00:18:31.282 position:21% line:89% align:start
You're on your own!

00:18:31.315 --> 00:18:33.784 position:7% line:83% align:start
This has little effect on our
mission.

00:18:33.818 --> 00:18:39.824 position:10% line:77% align:start
Even if we cannot return to
Earth... we will never hand
over Akari Hizamaru.

00:18:40.524 --> 00:18:45.396 position:30% line:5% align:start
(Bao Zhilian)
Targets acquired. Locking onto
Squad 1's coordinates now.

00:18:45.429 --> 00:18:48.666 position:30% line:89% align:start
 <i>[tracker beep]</i>

00:18:48.699 --> 00:18:52.704 position:5% line:83% align:start
Do it! Send that son of a bitch
to hell in a blaze of fire!

00:18:53.270 --> 00:18:54.605 position:41% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:18:55.373 --> 00:18:58.142 position:16% line:89% align:start
Yeah, I don't think so.

00:18:58.677 --> 00:19:00.746 position:24% line:89% align:start
Any last requests?

00:19:10.422 --> 00:19:13.825 position:35% line:83% align:start
The worst may finally
be behind us...for now.

00:19:14.426 --> 00:19:16.260 position:21% line:89% align:start
I hope you're right.

00:19:16.293 --> 00:19:17.929 position:35% line:89% align:start
Wanna know somethin'?

00:19:17.963 --> 00:19:22.401 position:16% line:83% align:start
I don't think I've ever been
more thankful to be alive.

00:19:22.434 --> 00:19:24.469 position:21% line:89% align:start
I feel the same way.

00:19:24.503 --> 00:19:27.939 position:47% line:83% align:start
[smirk] I bet you
do, you big sap.

00:19:27.973 --> 00:19:32.310 position:21% line:83% align:start
I hope... we can make your
friend's cure in time.

00:19:32.344 --> 00:19:35.213 position:35% line:89% align:start
Sakurato?

00:19:35.247 --> 00:19:36.615 position:41% line:89% align:start
 <i>Was that his name?</i>

00:19:36.648 --> 00:19:37.616 position:41% line:89% align:start
[sigh]

00:19:37.649 --> 00:19:41.420 position:5% line:89% align:start
Akari, we kept hope alive today.

00:19:41.453 --> 00:19:43.422 position:33% line:89% align:start
We sure did.

00:19:43.455 --> 00:19:45.757 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Michelle)</i>
 <i>Think you could take</i>
 <i>over for a bit?</i>

00:19:45.791 --> 00:19:47.126 position:5% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Akari)</i>
 <i>Oh, of course.</i>

00:19:47.160 --> 00:19:49.929 position:35% line:77% align:start
 <i>(Michelle)</i>
 <i>Thanks, I'm in dire</i>
 <i>need of a nap.</i>

00:19:54.499 --> 00:19:58.370 position:13% line:83% align:start
Out like a light. Funny...
she looks peaceful...

00:19:58.403 --> 00:19:59.739 position:27% line:89% align:start
And kinda cute.

00:20:01.640 --> 00:20:03.375 position:5% line:89% align:start
Eyes on the road.

00:20:03.408 --> 00:20:06.344 position:19% line:83% align:start
What the hell?! W-Why
are you still awake?!

00:20:06.378 --> 00:20:07.612 position:5% line:83% align:start
I can feel you
staring at me!

00:20:07.647 --> 00:20:09.548 position:38% line:83% align:start
(Akari)
I wasn't starring at you!

00:20:09.581 --> 00:20:12.785 position:35% line:83% align:start
Must be nice... being
young and in love.

00:20:12.819 --> 00:20:14.352 position:78% line:89% align:start
[gasp]

00:20:18.024 --> 00:20:21.961 position:24% line:71% align:start
 <i>(Shokichi Komachi)</i>
If everything goes smoothly,
 <i>we'll reconvene after taking th</i>
Annex 1.

00:20:21.994 --> 00:20:27.633 position:10% line:77% align:start
 <i> But if something happens and</i>
 <i> returning to the ship is not a</i>
 <i> viable option, head north.</i>

00:20:27.667 --> 00:20:30.002 position:24% line:83% align:start
North is our only
hope if we fail...

00:20:32.872 --> 00:20:35.475 position:27% line:83% align:start
 <i>(Marcos Garcia)</i>
 <i>Captain! What's the plan now?</i>

00:20:35.508 --> 00:20:38.711 position:33% line:89% align:start
North, now!

00:20:39.912 --> 00:20:41.647 position:24% line:89% align:start
And don't stop...

00:20:42.815 --> 00:20:44.350 position:13% line:89% align:start
We're heading to the sea!

00:20:46.086 --> 00:20:49.255 position:35% line:89% align:start
Let's go.

00:20:53.793 --> 00:20:59.665 position:44% line:89% align:start
 ♪

00:21:04.537 --> 00:21:06.539 position:38% line:89% align:start
[crash]

00:21:06.572 --> 00:21:08.142 position:33% line:89% align:start
Oh, come on!

00:21:08.175 --> 00:21:11.377 position:13% line:77% align:start
This is why you never buy
a "classic" car, they're
always breaking down!

00:21:11.410 --> 00:21:13.546 position:27% line:83% align:start
Relax. There's a
small town up ahead.

00:21:13.579 --> 00:21:15.749 position:24% line:83% align:start
I'm sure they have
a tow service.

00:21:25.592 --> 00:21:29.663 position:24% line:89% align:start
Jo! Jo-ji jo! Jo!

00:21:29.696 --> 00:21:31.031 position:19% line:89% align:start
What are they saying?

00:21:31.064 --> 00:21:33.500 position:5% line:89% align:start
That's not English...What is it?

00:21:33.534 --> 00:21:36.737 position:16% line:83% align:start
Let's go back. Come on.
They're probably squatters.

00:21:36.770 --> 00:21:40.707 position:10% line:77% align:start
It's been all over the news.
They find abandoned towns and
just ruin everything.

00:21:40.741 --> 00:21:43.610 position:13% line:83% align:start
I've heard people say that
they can be dangerous...

00:21:43.644 --> 00:21:45.412 position:7% line:77% align:start
Let's just get out of here...
[car engine starts]

00:21:45.445 --> 00:21:46.747 position:38% line:89% align:start
[gasps]

00:21:51.985 --> 00:21:53.987 position:38% line:89% align:start
Jo Ji...

00:21:54.788 --> 00:21:56.790 position:33% line:89% align:start
[screaming]

00:21:57.825 --> 00:22:03.730 position:27% line:89% align:start
 <i>[phone ringing]</i>

00:22:12.140 --> 00:22:15.043 position:24% line:83% align:start
Dinner's ready, if
you're hungry.

00:22:15.076 --> 00:22:17.511 position:24% line:83% align:start
 It's curry, your
favorite...

00:22:18.813 --> 00:22:22.851 position:7% line:83% align:start
I heard you didn't show up for
your exams this year...

00:22:22.884 --> 00:22:27.454 position:5% line:83% align:start
How do you expect to find a real
job if you never leave your room

00:22:27.487 --> 00:22:28.388 position:33% line:89% align:start
 <i>[loud crash]</i>

00:22:28.422 --> 00:22:32.392 position:21% line:83% align:start
S-sorry dear, I know
how busy you are...

00:22:33.027 --> 00:22:36.130 position:19% line:83% align:start
Just... call me if you
need anything.

00:22:42.170 --> 00:22:47.542 position:35% line:89% align:start
Jo-Ji! Jo?

00:22:47.575 --> 00:22:49.577 position:35% line:89% align:start
Ji-Jo Ji!

00:22:50.478 --> 00:22:54.582 position:24% line:89% align:start
[electric current]

00:23:06.594 --> 00:23:08.630 position:38% line:89% align:start
Chu-Ji!

00:23:10.565 --> 00:23:19.141 position:47% line:89% align:start
♪

00:23:19.174 --> 00:23:21.911 position:5% line:89% align:start
Good ol fashioned street brawl.

00:23:21.944 --> 00:23:26.882 position:7% line:89% align:start
 <i>If we're going to win this...</i>

00:23:26.916 --> 00:23:29.184 position:13% line:89% align:start
 <i>We'll need more fighters.</i>

00:23:29.218 --> 00:23:33.122 position:19% line:83% align:start
 <i>Every anti-terraformar</i>
 <i>expert we can find.</i>

00:23:33.155 --> 00:23:35.758 position:35% line:89% align:start
Come back!

00:23:37.625 --> 00:23:40.195 position:19% line:83% align:start
I don't know how much
longer I can hold on...

00:23:40.229 --> 00:23:47.435 position:7% line:89% align:start
So, please... hurry back home.

